      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI TO SUCCESS (8) settled well back at his most recent outing with a sustained effort and scored by a head in a nice return to form at Melton over 1720m. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and might sweat on the sprint lane. Leading hope in this comparable race. SANCHEZ (1) worked to find the lead and kept kicking only to find a couple better last time out over 2150m at Birchip, making it two minor placings in a row. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Finds a suitable assignment and will prove very tough to beat once more. ATA RANGI (5) is in the mix following a respectable second at his most recent appearance over 2240m at Melton. LOUIE LOU I NZ (7) must be considered after he finished third over 2240m at Melton two weeks ago.",
